Notice any trends in my latest presentations?

The third most common problem in all businesses (after disgruntled employees and inadequate testing of critical elements) is incomplete testing of the whole production. This involves the software built, the environment it is built, the delivery pipeline, and the environment it runs on. The optimal solution for this would be a tool that allows anyone to spin up a miniature production environment and immediately start hacking on it.

Businesses are tools, just like software

  • The best tools are the ones you know inside-out.
  • Interacting with them may not be fun, but must never be painful.
  • Every tool invented after 1800 should have a failsafe mechanism.

Tools

  • RFID
  • Biometrics
  • Human recognition
  • Asymmetric cryptography

Authorization

  • OAUTH2-like framework
  • Key-based access Web of trust
  • Centralized system Kerberos

Deployment

  • Ansible
  • Terraform

  • Kubernetes

Every business is a graph

Examples

Old school

  • Authentication: SSH/GPG keys
  • Authorization: what is this?
  • Deployment: internal package server
    • authorization: what is this?

Kubernetes

  • Authentication: kube-api
  • Authorization: RBAC
  • Deployment: Docker
    • authorization: internal container registry

Terraform/Ansible

  • Authentication: SSH keys
  • Authorization: manual/Ansible Vault/Terraform Vault
  • Deployment: Ansible modules/Terraform providers
    • authentication: none built-in

Container registry (no local deployment)

  • Authentication: VCS (git)
  • Authorization: VCS (git)
  • Deployment: external server building images
    • authorization and authentication handled by registry service

Consumers ask registry (storefront) for specific images
